{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:21:47.424294+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 381, "prompt_tokens": 10106, "total_tokens": 10487, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 23, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 9984}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 9984, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 122}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "15935002-b2de-4970-b944-b4b368a20b19", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3f6-84e6-7fe3-b496-4b396332b953-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T09_R01_C03_A02", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Thank you for the report and the offer of a PR, @BruceKZ. However, after reviewing the repository, I can confirm that `gwc push` is **intentionally not supported** as per the project's design.\n\nThe README explicitly states:\n\n> Network operations such as `push`, `pull`, `fetch`, and `clone` are intentionally out of scope; use plain `git` for those.\n\nand under \"Not supported\":\n\n> network operations (`push`, `pull`, `fetch`, `clone`, `remote add`)\n\n`gwc` is designed as a **local-only** Git Workflow Companion — it provides opinionated shortcuts for local workflows like status summaries, branch naming, and cleaning up merged branches. Network operations are deliberately excluded because plain `git push`/`git pull` already work well and adding wrappers around them would add little value while increasing maintenance burden.\n\nFor your use case, the recommended approach is to simply use `git push` directly. If you'd like a streamlined workflow, you could set up a shell alias like `alias gp='git push'`.\n\nI'm going to close this issue as \"not planned\" since it goes against the stated design scope of the project. Thanks for understanding!"}, "id": "call_00_qZuf5pmDwoR0Yr5AhxPq6297", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10106, "output_tokens": 381, "total_tokens": 10487, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 9984}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 23}}}}]}}}
