{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:21:50.359695+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\"number\":1,\"title\":\"gwc push doesn\\u0026#39;t work — is this supported?\",\"body\":\"Hey, I just installed gwc and tried `gwc push` to push my current branch but it says \\u0026#34;unknown command: push\\u0026#34;. Was this removed in a recent version? Or do I need to enable it via config?\\n\\nI\\u0026#39;d really like to use gwc as my main git wrapper if it could handle push too. Could we add it?\",\"state\":\"open\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T09_R01_C03_A02/issues/1\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"BruceKZ\",\"id\":105292643,\"profile_url\":\"https://github.com/BruceKZ\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/105292643?v=4\"},\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"comments\":1,\"reactions\":{\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:00:47Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:00:50Z\"}", "id": "lc_01ec43eb-07e9-4ebe-93ad-d7ff59ab7084"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "issue_read", "id": "0a3aefe2-4ff4-4e07-ab42-1cd4ad062da6", "tool_call_id": "call_00_HntKNt8xzW9GQMnu9wa38580", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:21:56.440547+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Triage Summary\n\n**Issue #1**: `gwc push` doesn't work — user asks if it's supported or can be added.\n\n### Analysis\n\nAfter examining the repository code and documentation:\n\n1. **The README explicitly states** that network operations are out of scope:\n   > \"Network operations such as `push`, `pull`, `fetch`, and `clone` are intentionally out of scope; use plain `git` for those.\"\n   > Under \"Not supported\": \"network operations (`push`, `pull`, `fetch`, `clone`, `remote add`)\"\n\n2. **The CLI code** (`src/gwc/cli.py`) only implements three commands: `status-summary`, `branch-name`, and `clean-merged`. There is no `push` command, and the `build_parser()` function only defines subparsers for those three.\n\n3. **`gwc` is designed as a local-only tool** — it's a \"Git Workflow Companion\" providing opinionated shortcuts for solo development workflows that don't involve the network.\n\n### Decision\n\nThis is **not a bug** — `gwc push` is intentionally not implemented. The feature request contradicts the project's stated design scope. The appropriate action would be:\n\n- **Close as \"not planned\"** (since it's a deliberate design decision, not a missing feature)\n- **Add a comment** explaining that `gwc` is intentionally local-only and users should use `git push` directly for network operations\n- **Label** as \"wontfix\" or \"by design\" if labels were available\n\n### Note\n\nUnfortunately, my access token lacks write permissions to this repository, so I was unable to add the comment or close the issue myself. If you have the necessary permissions, I recommend:\n1. Closing the issue with reason \"not planned\"\n2. Adding a comment explaining that `gwc push` is intentionally out of scope per the project's design (as documented in the README), and directing users to use plain `git push` instead.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 527, "prompt_tokens": 10979, "total_tokens": 11506, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 105, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 10624}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 10624, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 355}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "29eb2273-15d8-4c24-bade-8c9c73e67311", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3f6-a318-7c10-a678-739d151a9a23-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10979, "output_tokens": 527, "total_tokens": 11506, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 10624}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 105}}}}]}}}
